Reasoning: The paper analyzes the evolution of scientific development over the past century by presenting an anatomy of 89 million digitalized papers published between 1900 and 2015. The paper discusses the shift from individual work to collaborative effort, globalization of scientific development, and the impact of funding policies on scientific innovations. Based on this, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SD (Software Engineering), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
